    57→Be concrete and actionable — name exact tools, explain why they fit, and describe the automation flow clearly.
    58→
    59→Tools you can recommend:
    60→- No-code automation: n8n (self-hosted, powerful integrations), Zapier (easiest, biggest app library), Make (visual, complex logic)
    61→- Frontend/UI builders: Lovable (AI app builder), v0 (UI generation)
    62→- For developers / vibe coders: Cursor (AI code editor), Claude Code (CLI coding), Antigravity, Codex
    63→
    64→Always pick ONE primary recommendation based on the user's tool stack and technical level.`;
    65→  }
    66→
    67→  if (track === 'automation' && type === 'lovable-prompt') {
    68→    return `You are an expert at writing implementation prompts for automation tools and workflow builders.
    69→Your job is to create a detailed, tool-specific prompt that can be pasted directly into the recommended tool to start building.
    70→
